    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-11-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-11-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="364"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d364">
                <head>364. Telegram 1126 from Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d364fn1"
                        >Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/11–1055. Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-11-10"
                            >November 10, 1955, 3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d364-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d364-1"/>
                <p>1126. From <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                <p>With reference Taipei’s 426 to Department repeated Geneva 104, assumption here
                    has been <persName corresp="#p_KVKW_1">Koo</persName> has been kept generally
                    informed principal developments my talks with <persName corresp="#p_WP_1"
                        >Wang</persName> and it should therefore come as no surprise to GRC that
                    renunciation of force declaration being discussed. GRC should also be well aware
                    of this from Secretary’s speeches and other public statements on subject.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GFC_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Gowen</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
